Class FormattedNumber

  • java.lang.Object
    • filipondiosUtils.FormattedNumber
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<FormattedNumber>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Matrix

    public class FormattedNumber
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<FormattedNumber>
    Class that creates objets symulating fraction numbers and int numbers by parsing a String input with or without the character "/". This allows to the user to type any number as n/m or n.
    Version:
    07.06.2022
    Author:
    Filipondios
